  "title": "Senior Associate/Assistant Manager, Global Esports Broadcast Producer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee the end-to-end production of esports broadcasts, including live matches, studio shows, and supplementary content.</li>\n  <li>Develop broadcast rundowns, scripts, and content strategies to deliver engaging and high-quality viewing experiences.</li>\n  <li>Direct live broadcasts, coordinating various production elements such as camera angles, graphics, replays, and talent.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate broadcast schedules, ensuring smooth transitions between different programs and events.</li>\n  <li>Manage and maintain all broadcast technology and equipment, including cameras, mixers, encoders, graphics systems, and streaming platforms.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoot technical issues during live broadcasts and implement immediate solutions to minimize downtime.</li>\n  <li>Research and recommend new technologies and workflows to enhance broadcast quality and efficiency.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 3 years of experience in live broadcast production, preferably within the esports or sports industry.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to work flexible hours, including evenings and weekends, as required by tournament schedules. This role may involve frequent regional travel to various countries for work-related assignments.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in directing live shows and managing complex technical setups.</li>\n  <li>Strong working knowledge of live broadcast production software/hardware (e.g., vMix, OBS, EVS, NDI, comms, streaming encoders, etc.).</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with cloud streaming, remote production workflows, and signal distribution across platforms.</li>\n  <li>Ability to integrate new technologies and optimize broadcast workflows in both online and studio settings.</li>\n  <li>Good understanding of the Battle Royale genre and its competitive esports ecosystem.</li>\n  <li>Strong problem-solving and crisis management skills during live events.</li>\n  <li>Experience working in global or cross-regional esports tournaments is highly preferred.</li>\n</ul>",
